Cryptotaenia japonica

    Authority   Hassk
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Apiales:Umbelliferae
     Synonyms   Cryptotaenia canadensis D.C. var. japonica Makino
   Common names mitsuba, Japanese honeworts, Japanese parsley
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4999

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an evergreen perennial reaching up to 0.5-1 m in
   height and 0.6 m in width. USE: It is grown for its edible long,
   slender, edible petioles and leaflets. Also the root and stem is
   edible. The seed is used as a seasoning. It also has medicinal
   properties and is widely grown as a perennial leaf garden ornamental
   and also indoors as a potted plant. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial but
   usually cultivated as an annual. COMMON NAMES: Mitsuba, Japanese
   honeworts, Japanese parsley. FURTHER INF: It is found wild in woodland
   in hills and mountains where it can be found in light to deep shade and
   along shady edges.

   Sources
   http://www.hort.purdue.edu/newcrop/proceedings1990/V1-387.html
   http://www.ibiblio.org/pfaf/cgi-bin/arr_html?Cryptotaenia+japonica

